The paper deals with the problem of quantifying interesting subpopulations in high dimensional data using the Mapper, which is a tool from computational topology. This involves creating a weighted directed graph and studying optimization problems on this graph. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
